    {"id": "ja_jh_001", "levels": [{"front": "Doctor", "back": "医者 / 医師", "romanized": "isha / ishi", "grammarNote": "In Japanese, professions are stated without an article: 'watashi wa isha desu' (私は医者です, I am a doctor). Unlike English, no 'a' or 'an' is needed. 'Isha' (医者) is the common everyday word; 'ishi' (医師) is the formal/official term."}, {"front": "He is a doctor.", "back": "彼は医者です。", "romanized": "kare wa isha desu", "literal": "He [topic] doctor is."}]},
